git status 
git init
git add "<filename>"/ git add . (For all files)
git commit [-m (for a title message)]
git config --global user.email "you@example.com" (First Time)
git config --global user.name "Your Name" (First Time)
git log (Record of all changes)
git diff (View the last change made)
git diff id1 id2 (View the changes between any two commits)

git remote add <Repository Name> <Remote Repository Link> (Add RR)
git remote (View all RR linked to this project)
git remote -v (Verbose/ View RR Link)
git push -u origin master (First time)
